OpenSRS is a Tucows company. Join the go-to platform for resellers of Domain Names, Hosted Email, SSL Certificates and Security and Privacy Products. We are one of the reseller customer of OpenSRS. 

All our domain names and the customer domain name, SSL certificates are purchased from OpenSRS. 

Customer can manage their registered domain name through the opensrs domain management control panel - https://manage.opensrs.net 

Login to there using the domainname, username and the password.


## How Change the OpenSRS Login Password

The password can be changed after login to the opensrs panel.

Click on the Profilelink and click on Change Password.
Then you will get a new option to set new password.

## How to Create Sub User

**Note**: Only one sub-user can be created for each domain.

You may add an additional username and password associated with this domain in order to allow multiple people to update your records. You can restrict access for this sub-user to allow only certain records to be modified. 

- Login to the OpenSRS panel >> Go to Profile >> Click on Create/Manage a Sub-User
- Then submit your username, password and select the sub user permissions in the new form and submit the details. 

```diagram

```


You can also delete the already created sub user if need from the same window. 

## How to Change  Domain Whois Details

Domain whois (Organization | Admin | Billing | Technical) details can be update from the opensrs panel. 

- Login to the OpenSRS panel.
- Click on any of the link named **Organization** | **Admin** | **Billing** | **Technical**
- Then you will get the current details. Update the details you want and the click on the button **Save Configuration**

## How to Create Custom Name Servers Based on the Domain Name

- Login to the Opensrs Panel. Then go to **Name Servers** >> Click on **Manage Name Servers**
- You will get the current registered name server. 
- Scroll down the window until you see the message "*If you want to create or modify a nameserver which is based on domainname.com click here*" 
- Click on the Link. then you will get a new window to set-up custom name servers on your domain name.
- Write the new name servers and put the IP address correctly and then click on the button **Create Name Server**
